text: Moved to this area recently and visited this place on a Sunday morning. There were a lot of people as it is nearby a wet market. They have a wide range of food selection. In the morning, they have noodles, nasi lemak, varieties of kueh and dessert. Even iced one. Didn’t expect that when I ordered a sea coconut. Anyway, it was really hot that day. So I just went with the flow. Happy to find big pieces of sea coconut but it is weird that they have other fruits in the dessert. I wouldn’t recommend to have the lime in it cos it just covers the sea coconut flavour. Plus point, it is cheap. $2 for dessert and $0.80 for white sugar steamed cake.

A really one of a kind snack bar in Singapore with all kinds of traditional kueh and Chinese snacks available. I recall there’s one in Hougang Ave 2 and never thought there’s another one right here in Bangkit!

The shop sells literally every kind of snack you can think of: there’s the usual bread buns and pastries outside, Nyonya kueh and carrot cake, Peng kueh, dumplings in the cabinet and a bread station at one end putting jams and spreads to freshly baked bread.

Prices are pretty affordable, bought 4 pieces of kueh (the yellow ones) and it’s $3.20 only. Much cheaper than the other kueh chain B.S. If you like old school snacks, this is the place to go!
Love coming back for their vegetarian beehoon. There are also econic noodles, varieties of kueh, soya bean drink and agar agar. Their rest day is on every monday.
Their glutinous rice is so yummy. Always buy some when I come here. They have white & dark sauce flavours. Both are good. $2 each.
Bought ondeh ondeh and ang ku kueh from there. The ondeh has a rotten coconut smell upon first bite . This was my 1 st and last time buying from this stall. Not worth my money.
